  "summary": "Malicious code in @playerdata-internal/playerdata-core (npm)",
  "details": "Dependency-confusion package targeting internal @playerdata-internal scoped names. On install, the postinstall hook runs index.js which collects system metadata (username, hostname, local IP address, platform, current working directory) and exfiltrates it via HTTPS POST to webhook[.]site/a8cd7fd0-4d41-4806-8649-f3297e94a008. The package has no legitimate functionality — its only code is the reconnaissance and exfiltration payload.",
